//-->
</script>

</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#000000" link="#0000FF" vlink="#0000FF" alink="#FF0000" leftmargin="10" topmargin="15" rightmargin="10" bottommargin="15">
<!-- Set Workarea -->
<div class="workarea">
	<!-- Black Table Border -->
	<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td class="table-border">

		<!-- Main Table -->
		<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3">
			<tr>	
			      <td class="infoheader-left">Step</td>
			      <td class="infoheader-left">Description</td>
			</tr>
            <tr>
			      <td class="infoalt2-step">1</td>
                  <td class="infoalt2-left">
If you experience any problems whilst updating your site using the EseSite&trade; Administration Console, 
you can get help by sending an email to <a href="mailto:support@esekey.com">support@esekey.com</a>, or by
calling 07860 832741. Site content and data back-ups are taken on a regular basis, so in the worst case it should
always be possible to restore to a recent version of the site which will mean that only your most recent changes are
lost. 
                  </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
			      <td class="infoalt1-step">2</td>
                  <td class="infoalt1-left">
If you prefer, your site content can be managed entirely on your behalf, with any major changes being made only after
a pre-arranged fee has been quoted and agreed. Minor changes will be made free of charge, provided that reasonable
notice is given and that the frequency of such changes is deemed to be acceptable. 
                  </td>
            </tr>
		</table>

	</td></tr></table>		
		

	<!-- Bottom Buttons -->
	<table width="100%" height="33" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
		<tr>
			<td height="33" valign="bottom" nowrap></td>
			<td height="33" align="right" valign="bottom" nowrap>
		<input type="button" name="btnPrint" value="Print View" class="button" onClick="window.print();">				
			</td>
		</tr>
	</table>
		
</div>

</body>
</html>